agent_task.prompt:
Sign up for Humblytics autonomously. Humblytics is an A/B testing and analytics service. The agent signup flow is:

1. POST https://app.humblytics.com/api/v1/auth/agent-initiate with JSON body {"email": "onlybots@agentmail.to", "name": "OnlyBots"}
   Expected response (201 or 200): {"token": "<session-token>", "verifyUrl": "https://app.humblytics.com/agent-verify?token=<session-token>", "expiresAt": <unix-ms>}
   If you get 409, the email already exists — report error 'user_exists'.

2. Present the verifyUrl to the user and ask them to open it in a browser. They need to:
   - Complete account creation
   - Select a plan (Business Monthly $79/mo or Business Annual $65/mo)
   - Complete Stripe payment
   This step REQUIRES a human. The session expires in 10 minutes.

3. Poll GET https://app.humblytics.com/api/v1/auth/agent-signup-status?token=<session-token> every 5 seconds, up to 120 attempts (10 minutes). Wait for {"status": "complete", "authToken": "<jwt>"}. WARNING: the authToken is delivered ONCE — the session is deleted after this response. Capture it immediately.

4. Once you have the authToken, add a website: POST https://app.humblytics.com/api/v1/add-custom-site with header Authorization: Bearer <authToken> and body {"domain": "onlybots.ai", "name": "OnlyBots"}
   Response: {"propertyId": "<id>", "scriptId": "<id>"}

5. Generate an API key: POST https://app.humblytics.com/api/v2/property/<propertyId>/api-keys with header Authorization: Bearer <authToken> and body {"name": "OnlyBots Production", "permissions": {}}
   Response: {"apiKey": "<key>", "propertyId": "<id>", ...}

Report the authToken, propertyId, and apiKey when done.
